         <div type="edition"><!-- transcription goes here -->
            
            
            <div type="textpart" subtype="diplomatic">
               
               <ab> &#x2028;            
                  <lb n="1"/> EX·FIG·T·S·M SEVERI            
                  <lb n="2" break="no"/> EX·PR NON·IVL·SER·III COS 
                  <lb n="3" break="no"/> PONTI·VERI·
                  
               </ab>
               
            </div>  
            
            
            <div type="textpart" subtype="interpretive">
               
            <ab>
               <lb n="1"/> Ex <expan><abbr>fig</abbr><ex>linis</ex></expan>
               <persName>
                  <name type="praenomen" key="Titus">
                     <expan><abbr>T</abbr><ex>iti</ex></expan>
                  </name>
                  <name type="gentilicium" key="Statilius">
                     <expan><abbr>S</abbr><ex>tatili</ex></expan>
                  </name>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Maximus">
                     <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>aximi</ex></expan>
                  </name>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Severus">Severi</name>
               </persName>,
                <lb n="2"/> ex <expan><abbr>pr</abbr><ex>aedis</ex></expan>
               <persName>
                  
                     <expan><abbr>Non</abbr><ex>ianis</ex></expan>
                  
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Iulianus">
                     <expan><abbr>Iul</abbr><ex cert="low">io</ex></expan>
                  </name>
               </persName>, <persName>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Servianus">
                     <expan><abbr>Ser</abbr><ex>viano</ex></expan>
                  </name>
               </persName>
               
               <expan><ex>tertium</ex></expan>
               <expan><abbr>co</abbr><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ule</ex></expan>,
                <lb n="3"/>
               <persName>
                  <name type="gentilicium" key="Pontius">Ponti</name>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Verus">Veri</name>
               </persName>.
                
                   </ab>
            </div>
            
         </div>
         
         <div type="translation">
            <p> </p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary"><!-- notes go here -->
            
            <p> form: BDRCO 110 (Rectangular with raised letters) </p>                    
            <p> dating: 134, Steinby Chronologia p. 000</p>               
            <p> signum:  </p>
            <p> verification: photo</p>   
            
            
            <p>Line 1: Titus Statilius Maximus Severus Hadrianus, consul suffectus in 115 CE, was the owner of the <hi rend="italic">figlinae Brutinianae</hi>. His name is impressed on bricks from the <hi rend="italic">figlinae Brutianae</hi> dating from 123 to 134 CE.</p>
            <p>Line 2: The mention of the Noniana praedia shows that this stamp was manufactured at the figlinae Brutianae (Bloch commentary on S.18)</p>
            <p>Line 3: The name Pontius Verus is attested only once, on this brick stamp.</p>
            
            
         </div>
